', 'Be safe, protect yourself and those around you by TAKING CARE OF YOURSELF!

#HealthyAtHome
#COVID„É?9
#coronavirus
', 'I have always had a tissue in my bag and hand sanitizer, and I have always had a craze for washing my hands at the slightest provocation.

If you haven‚Äôt cultivated the habits that could keep us relatively safe by now, then you are the problem!
#COVID„É?9
', 'Right now I‚Äôm drinking my tea infused with black pepper, taking my vitamins every night before bed so I wake up energised, cooking with as much natural herbs and condiments as the meal can contain (my favourite is cloves, chilli flakes and parsley)
#COVID„É?9
', 'I have always known I had a weak immune system, maybe not dangerously so, but enough to make me quite susceptible to the commonest of illnesses. How have I managed? A lifetime of fruits, natural herbs and condiments that boost immunity, and vitamins. #COVID„É?9
', 'If nothing else, #COVID„É?9 will teach us to be more exacting with our personal hygiene and wellbeing. Healthcare systems across the globe are suffering because we have become more reliant on doctor‚Äôs prescription and ignoring the simple healthy habits that keep everyone healthy.
']

", 'Looking at the face of this Ugandan woman breaks my heart on the untold hardship similar Nigerian/African women who only make a living from daily market sales would definitely go thru as #COVID19 lock down rages in many African nations. column2:
['I remember where I was when 9-11 happened. I remember every single second of that day. Every single family member of a #COVID19 victim remembers where they were when their loved one died alone. #RNC2020
', '@icecube I have loved and supported you my whole life. I could quote Friday after Next word for word. My mom, my aunt, and my grandma died from #COVID19... I feel very uncomfortable with your recent statements. Call me.
', "RT @chuckcreekmur: By the way, I noticed @JoeBiden offered his condolences to everybody that has lost loved ones to #COVID19. I don't think‚Ä¶
", 'Hard watching the #DemConvention... lots of talk about #COVID19... I miss my Momma. Every single second of every single day, I miss my dear girl. https://t.co/Z854mWuvXW
', 'It‚Äôs never my intention to go viral when I post about the fact that my mother, grandmother, and my favorite aunt all died from #COVID19 it‚Äôs just a sad fact... and I miss my family.
', 'My mom helped my aunt get ready for her 50th wedding anniversary last year. They are both dead now. They died from #COVID19 this year... but @realDonaldTrump ‚ÄúIt is what it is...‚Ä?https://t.co/3uVeHXf362
', 'Let me tell you something about #COVID19. These are not just 150K people. Each of those people had families, friends, coworkers, favorite restaurants, habits, stories, and dreams. We didn‚Äôt just lose our loved ones, we lost a part of our hearts.
', 'My mom died in April from #COVID19. She was in a group that put out a gospel album album in 1987 and I hadn‚Äôt heard it in years. It‚Äôs still amazing.
']

["Why do people love #TigerKingNetflix?
When the #coronavirus crisis is existentially overwhelming beyond our human control, we find comfort in a story of taking control of one's destiny and taming nature. Not sure I'd want this destiny though.

@netflix #MFACadets36 https://t.co/kTOAjd9knp
", 'Drove my wife to get checked for the coronavirus at the new drive through check. Want to thank the volunteers and employees of @Mdais for their incredible dedication.

#coronavirus #COVID #StayHome #MFACadets36 https://t.co/8wmokWHzNh
', 'During the quarantine I realized I am lucky I have a balcony and I can enjoy the fresh air.

What makes you feel lucky these days?

#MFACadets36
#coronavirus
#stayhomesavelives
#covid19 https://t.co/ur5z5ultaB
', "Google photos: that's how your life looked like a year ago.
Me: but I am in quarantine.
Google: all the travel.
Me:

#Covid_19 #MFACadets36 https://t.co/KW6p1lZKB1
", 'Reduction of emissions is a silver lining of this crisis?
Not sure. The economic price to be paid will be too pronounced and it is  short term reduction.
Perhaps what is needed is a qualitative change not a quantitative one.

#coronavirus #ClimateChange #MFAcadets36 https://t.co/tOG3qtkTVh
']

column2:
['There couldn‚Äôt  be a better time is for business leaders to put their values  in action. This is an insightful read about the ways that firms take action with their people and their ecosystem and #CSR in the wake of #COVID19. #GivingBack https://t.co/73H6ez20WJ
', 'Unsurprisingly, many #SmallBusinesseses are developing more digital products and services to better serve a quarantined customer base. But even after #coronavirus has passed, this trend will continue to shape American businesses. Thanks, @Bianca_B_Miller. https://t.co/jj6mTYf4Ki https://t.co/YS0eBU6EnQ
', 'Companies that are generous and compassionate will undoubtedly attract the interest of investors who share their values. If not motivated to just do the right thing, the peer pressure of supporting employees and customers is making leaders act #COVID19. https://t.co/XxS7HRmWbV
', 'Emotionally intelligent, sensitive leaders will win the day always and especially in the age of #coronavirus. Everyone needs a leader who understands themself and has empathy for others and can see the bigger picture for the good of all of us. https://t.co/RjwxOWxMou
', 'There is no coincidence that all of these successful responses to #COVID19 has been lead by women. Leaders around the world should be looking to emulate the decisions made and embody these characteristics. #ConnectingDuringCorona https://t.co/DlGFUq9b2z
', 'Have you heard of #PayItForward? During the #COVID19 pandemic, this is an initiative where large companies pay their small business vendors immediately. My blog offers more on how leaders and corporations are supporting #SmallBusinesses during this time.
https://t.co/DAYzHEYU4Y
', 'The #COVID19 pandemic offers business leaders a chance to collaborate and consciously serve those in need. Large corporations can help #SmallBusinesses during this time. Check out my latest blog for more details:
https://t.co/DAYzHEYU4Y
', 'Although my friend @RajSisodiaCC wrote this piece many months before anyone had heard of #COVID19, it is more salient now than ever. #BreatheInBreatheOut #ConnectDuringCorona
https://t.co/MUi6V6NhXw
']

column2:
['Can you help me say "Happy Birthday" to Kath?

She has been out there working during the #COVID19nz lockdown. She deserves so much.

If you have a COVID hero, let them know (use #mycovidhero). There's nothing more heart-warming than showing gratitude. https://t.co/wOBDeDbEnA
', '(5 / 5) How will you make use of these self-isolation days?

See my the other posts from this thread for ideas üëåüåª

#Covid_19 #coronavirus #SocialDistancing #SelfIsolation
', "(4 / 5) Take care of yourself. Make use of this time. Use airplane mode when you're ready to take flight into your journey of self-discovery. Don't waste this opportunity to reap the benefits of #solitude. Take charge of your experience. Take charge of your life.⁣

#Covid_19 https://t.co/63Diq7SppC
", "(3 / 5) Don't forget that SARS was a #coronavirus too, that you made it through, and that social media algorithms ensure you fall deeper into whatever emotion you're experiencing. What you are served is a reflection of what you order. Be mindful of your mindset.⁣

#Covid_19
", '(2 / 5) Things you might work on during this time:⁣
⁣
-Finishing a manuscript/painting/project⁣
-Learning a new skill
-Improving your immune system with exercise and nutrition⁣
-Enjoying time alone in nature⁣
-Journaling
-Writing apology and forgiveness letters⁣

#Covid_19 https://t.co/nc6Fhq09zh
', "(1 / 5) #Socialdistancing can feel like a punishment. When we misbehaved as children, many of us were forced by our parents into #quarantine.⁣
⁣
#Solitude is a precious thing, but when we don't choose it, it's easy to feel overwhelmed and anxious for it to end.⁣

#Covid_19 https://t.co/QRZ0D7VFjJ
"]

', 'Heard about the Union Home Minister Shri @AmitShah Ji being tested positive for #COVID-19. Wishing him a speedy recovery. My prayers are with him and his family!
', "Shocked to know that the Central Govt has dropped topics like Citizenship, Federalism, Secularism & Partition in the name of reducing CBSE course during #COVIDCrisis.
We strongly object to this & appeal @HRDMinistry, GoI to ensure these vital lessons aren't curtailed at any cost. https://t.co/pkBaVI4VKM
", "We've implemented a robust economic strategy to tackle #COVID19 & the devastation caused by Amphan. Proof lies in West Bengal's Unemployment Rate for the month of June 2020 which stands at 6.5%, far better than that of India at 11%, UP at 9.6% & Haryana at 33.6%, as per CMIE.
", 'Our health infra is fully prepared to tackle #COVID19, but we put equal emphasis on effective prevention from the virus too. Social distancing, safe practices & masks are the best ways to fight the pandemic. However, we feel, procuring masks may not be feasible for many. (1/2)
', "I would like to welcome back the OC of Bowbazar, Inspector Sidhartha Chakraborthy as he rejoins service after recovering from COVID-19.
No words are enough to express my gratitude towards the service of WB's police personnel in our fight against #COVID19
#BanglaKorbeJoyNischoi https://t.co/m4Cwpc89lg
", 'Today on #NationalDengueDay I would like to commend our health workers who are working tirelessly to combat Dengue amidst the #COVID19 pandemic.

Effective community engagement is the key to Dengue prevention & I urge everyone to protect themselves & follow preventive measures https://t.co/4o2wLTlOUz
', 'We welcome all constructive support & suggestions, especially from the Central Govt in negating the #Covid19 crisis. However, the basis on which Centre is proposing to deploy IMCTs in select districts across India including few in WB under Disaster Mgmt Act 2005 is unclear.(1/2)
']

column2:
['Sumado a la precariedad de los servicios de salud en mi tierra, el problema del #coronavirus ya ha desbordado la capacidad de atenci√≥n de los servicios m√©dicos en #Apurimac

Preste atencion presidente @MartinVizcarraC, aqu√≠ el testimonio en un Hospital en #Abancay.
@WalterMartosR https://t.co/JHMWI9AM5K
', 'La triste realidad de nuestro pa√≠s es que hay mucha gente que no ha tomado conciencia de la magnitud de la epidemia del #COVID19, por eso la irresponsabilidad y esta a la orden del d√≠a en todos lados.

Es duro, porque exponen la vida de todos y todas e indigna. https://t.co/3onBxR8ap9
', 'Debi√≥ haber reconociendo el error de abrir el transporte terrestre y a√©reo, que ha trasladado el virus a regiones.

Se requiere, postergar la fase 4, cuentas con DNI, un verdadero REACTIVA, bonos a vulnerables y fortalecer la estrategia comunitaria para rastrear al #COVID„É?9
2/2 https://t.co/RBxzKUaQgd
', '¬°La angurria pudo m√°s que la raz√≥n!

En plena pandemia, cuando el congresista tiene que ser responsable de no exponer a la poblaci√≥n al #COVID„É?9,se les ocurre las semanas se representaci√≥n en el @congresoperu, todo por plata

Loable las renuncias, se llama respeto x el elector https://t.co/YIitqcXaHt
', 'Esta es otra de las poderosas razones de la situaci√≥n ca√≥tica que estamos viviendo con el #COVID19.

Desde que se levanto la cuarentena ¬øa cu√°nto irresponsable hemos visto en las calles, con indignaci√≥n?

Y ojo, esto no ten√≠an nada que ver con la necesidad de trabajar de algunos. https://t.co/6q90NjYzWi
', 'Primero fue Glider Ushu√±ahua y ahora Moises Mamani, seg√∫n informan, tambi√©n por el #COVID„É?9, enfermedad que no distingue a nadie. Cuidemonos, que descansen en paz.

Es oportuno tambi√©n recordar que el 2018, falleci√≥ mi compa√±ero y gran amigo Mario Canzio, que Dios lo tenga. https://t.co/FdokjLsqFv
', 'Las denuncias por corrupci√≥n est√°n al orden del d√≠a, en plena pandemia del #Covid_19

En mi regi√≥n #Apurimac, ayer allanaron los domicilios del Gobernador Baltazar Lantaron, familiares y funcionarios presuntamente involucrados por la compra de ambulancias.
https://t.co/OtflTyvm7a
', 'Y vamos a seguir con estos n√∫meros de espanto del #Covid_19, ayer 9441 contagiados y 277 muertos

Al parecer en el gobierno, no saben que hacer, por eso destacan el confinamiento los domingos, es imperioso implementar el enfoque comunitario @MartinVizcarraC, para rastrear casos https://t.co/jtnv6gxyN1
', 'Estamos llegando a situaciones extremas, por la desesperaci√≥n de ver a un familiar cercano internado con el #COVID„É?9; lamentablemente desde el @gobiernoPeru no han establecido un protocolo para informar la situaci√≥n de salud de los pacientes internados https://t.co/I7lDNjVvjO
', 'RT @Ojo_Publico: #MapasCovid19 Con 43 decesos asociados a #Covid19 por cada 10 mil habitantes, Chincha Alta en Ica es la ciudad m√°s afectad‚Ä¶
', '¬øEl @congresoperu vive otra realidad?

Nada q ver, ya no saben como sacar plata, ahora para cobrar gastos x "semana de representaci√≥n".

Les importa un car.. la situaci√≥n que estamos viviendo con el incremento del #COVID19.Eso q la mayor√≠a est√°n en sus regiones y todo es virtual https://t.co/uWrNoZd3js
', 'Ministra #Mazzetti lo primero es que NO vuelvan a autorizar medidas "temerarias" como el transporte interprovincial, en bus o los vuelos a√©reos, en toda su capacidad.

Lo que vivimos en provincia estos d√≠as de repunte del #COVID19 es consecuencia de estas medidas incongruentes https://t.co/ZXrQOywxat
']

', '#COVID-19 is disproportionately threatening vulnerable communities like #trans, #LGBTQ, #Black, #Latinx, & #Immigrants. We should be doing everything we can to provide treatment to whoever needs it, not escalating fear & confusion. #ProtectTransHealth https://t.co/84Xcl9DnYR https://t.co/9L8bKKIZkx
', 'Every person deserves the right to life-saving testing & treatment as we navigate #COVID19, but the Trump admin wants trans people to be denied medical care because of who they are. Tell health insurance companies not now, not ever! #ProtectTransHealth https://t.co/84Xcl9DnYR https://t.co/f4gpgJoHR9
', 'The ethical thing to do is to ration care, when needed, based on individual odds of surviving #COVID19 infection ‚Ä?not based on someone‚Äôs baseline life expectancy, expected quality of life, or other assumptions based on their #disability. https://t.co/1dsHd74s9S
', 'Let‚Äôs be clear, the need for time to care and heal did not begin with the #coronavirus and it will not end here. We need #paidleave and #paidsickdays to last beyond this moment. We need the #PAIDLeaveAct, permanent policies that value our health, labor and loved ones. https://t.co/8o99I20bF1
', '.@CDCgov tells us to stay home if we have symptoms of #COVID19. Yet doing so will cost millions of workers their pay or their job. We need the #PAIDLeave Act to ensure #PaidLeaveforAll. https://t.co/CWRyJcS1BY
', 'ICE has proven itself incapable - or unwilling - of keeping #trans detainees safe. Now even DHS‚Äôs own experts say: ‚ÄúReleasing all immigration detainees who do not pose a security risk should be seriously considered in the effort to stop #coronavirus." #FreeThemAll #FreeKelly https://t.co/jhNBgUrvnb
', "We know that things are uncertain with the developments around #COVID19, and it can be difficult to process. We've put together some resources for you. Please RT and share to spread the word.
", "We need paid sick leave NOW. #Trans people are more likely to work low-wage jobs that don't have benefits & are being hurt by the #coronavirus pandemic. Senators: Say NO to the Johnson Amendment #FamiliesFirstBill https://t.co/wMncs14dFa
", 'Our country is facing a public health emergency with the #coronavirus pandemic. This is a time to unite, not divide. These harmful bills targeting #trans youth are not what we should be focusing on.

üö®@GovernorLittle, veto HB500 now!üö® https://t.co/ajSCPPuoXz #VetoHB500 #IDLeg https://t.co/E8WV1cDBZU

', '#COVID19 has highlighted the threats posed by the unchecked use of digital technology - surveillance, human rights abuses, cybercrime.

To address the challenges of the digital age, we urgently need increased cooperation and governance to connect, respect, and protect people. https://t.co/Ak9tBuGhsW
', 'We have seen such a widespread and damaging expansion of #COVID19 in large part because our multilateral system is not strong enough.

We need a strong, coordinated and coherent global response based on solidarity.

https://t.co/WrCRBwYesA
', '370 million school children are now missing out on school meals - a major source of nutrition - due to #COVID19 closures.

The response to the pandemic must support children who no longer have access to school meals.
', '#COVID19 is exposing the fragility of our world ‚Ä?our institutions, our health systems, and even our failing response to the climate crisis.

These challenges require unity and solidarity.

https://t.co/UJYB4gJy5g
', 'There is more than enough food in the world to feed our population of 7.8 billion.

But, today, more than 820 million people are hungry & #COVID19 is making things worse.

To eradicate hunger, we must ensure inclusive access to healthy and nutritious food.
', '#COVID19 is a threat to food security and nutrition, especially to the most vulnerable.

Without immediate action, we could soon face a massive global food emergency with disastrous long term impacts on hundreds of millions of children and adults.

https://t.co/wYGezfdu8U https://t.co/6VHdmJJb5J
', 'Sea levels are rising due to climate change.

Oceans are becoming more acidic & teeming with plastic.

As we work to end the #COVID19 pandemic & build back better, we have an unprecedented opportunity to protect the ocean on which millions of lives and livelihoods depend. https://t.co/EMIsWXEy6B
']

['The best part of a challenge is that it comes with a solution.. Digital is the ultimate equaliser in this pandemic... #COVID19

https://t.co/4WxqjRtv6U https://t.co/XYkpWL4EEv
', 'We can either get bogged down by a crisis or consider it a stepping stone to opportunities.. Ironically, being positive in our mindset is the best antidote to the virus. #COVID19 https://t.co/1Mm0dmEGXe
', 'Grateful & proud!

@techmahindracsr helped to clean 300+ community toilets in the slums of Mumbai & Pune under a special @UN program..

Hygiene is our first line of defence in the fight against #COVID__19. Thx @UNICEFIndia @CSRHealthAwards for the opportunity & recognition üôè https://t.co/2Vu09PSgNQ
', "#COVID19 has reiterated the significance of digitization in EVERYTHING we do,but more significantly in health care.

@marxtango & @PaddyPadmanabha's book Healthcare Digital Transformation is a compelling narrative that defines the future of healthcare.

All the best Ed & Paddyüëç https://t.co/kxqv1RykdV
", "Empowering the fourth estate..

@tech_mahindra is conducting exclusive screening through #Mhealthy for a community that's been almost as fearless as our medical fraternity during #COVID19.. Our warriors from media üôè

#PressClubOfIndia https://t.co/o058PTdMM0 https://t.co/yEsJm6uWj7
", "Driving positive change with a Covid 'Seatbelt'...

Happy to launch #Mhealthy - a #COVID19 screening from @tech_mahindra that uses #AI and #MachineLearning to monitor the overall health of the community..

https://t.co/SSSmPkubgN https://t.co/rkiZ8ifTJN
", '#COVID19 has accelerated automation in the kitchen too.. But will this taste of freedom from chores take away the inherent essence of cooking..? https://t.co/x9HZwhx0h3
', 'More power to you @SerumInstIndia  @adarpoonawalla

Serum Institute of India has been chosen by Oxford and its partner AstraZeneca to manufacture #covid19 vaccine once it gets ready.

#FightAgainstCOVID19 https://t.co/pO45LQWKaY
', 'Finding a #coronavirus vaccine is key, but its equitable global distribution will be equally crucial..

Again technology will pave the way.. #Blockchain will be key.
Insightful article coauthored by a @tech_mahindra colleague &
@wef fellow @AmeyRajput

https://t.co/0oTA7RBPeZ https://t.co/6zLFLK7MHN
', "As #COVID19 continues to dominate our lives, ensuring safety & easing things for our colleagues become doubly critical.

A small step @tech_mahindra - Introduction of a Special leave category of a few weeks for associates who've tested #COVID +ve.

#WellnessFirst. Always. https://t.co/ZinSp0QZo5
", 'Love how technology is being leveraged across audiences during #COVID ..

Virtual classroom teaching using #AR #VR in #Kerala https://t.co/taeOaUHf49
', "From the time we're born, till we breathe our last, and throughout in between, we're in their care. During the times of #COVID19, they've played 'larger than life' roles.

Am always thankful to them, but today on #NationalDoctorsDay my special #ThankYou to all doctors üôè https://t.co/lZHsWYvUdz
", '@CNBCTV18News @Sudhir_Nayar @TVMohandasPai @Nithin0dha Innovation was always borderless..

#COVID19 has actually challenged conventional thinking. We saw increased innovation in solns /team connects & had collaborative disruption from our Innovation lab (MakersLab) for AI based protein analysis amongst others!

#CiscoFutureOfWork
', '@nehagurmeet @CNBCTV18News @TVMohandasPai @Nithin0dha @iamsayed @tanvi_gautam @Sudhir_Nayar @NJayantha @CNBCTV18Live Absolutely... And fortunately Diversity & gig working have been an unintended beneficiary of #COVID19 Geographic boundaries no longer a barrier to talent..

Diversity of gender, generation, nationality and thought are all important..Cobots & Humans together..

#CiscoFutureOfWork
', '@CNBCTV18News @tanvi_gautam @Sudhir_Nayar @NJayantha @Nithin0dha @iamsayed @TVMohandasPai In our case, training was always virtual & appified. Hv seen a significant uptake during #Covid19.

We have a self driven training prog that cuts across bands & associates are encouraged to choose from a bouquet of offerings from our #NewAgeDelivery Platform

#ciscoFutureOfWork
', '@CNBCTV18News @TVMohandasPai @Nithin0dha @iamsayed @tanvi_gautam @Sudhir_Nayar @NJayantha Collaboration tools have been the Oxygen of all businesses..

It enabled remote working for 125k emps @tech_mahindra We went from 0.2% adoption of Teams to 100% in a week‚Äôs time.. #COVID19 19 was probably the best Publicist @Microsoft could have hired!

#CiscoFutureOfWork
', 'Siyaram‚Äôs launches Anti-Corona fabric...

While it‚Äôs heartening to see organisations being responsive to #COVID19 and evolving their product line, such promises come with a huge responsibility because they raise hope..

Hope corporate conscience trumps marketing copy. https://t.co/6SYD9JlPOa
', "While #PresidentTrump's ban on #H1Bvisas is unfortunate, #COVID__19 has made us 'Atmanirbhar'..  Curbs on H-1B visa will not disrupt Indian IT sector.

https://t.co/744glYll5U
", "This was a 'radio' connect with the team @tech_mahindra .. By the end of  #Covid19 I think we would have explored every way of reaching out..

Thank U Umang team for the session and for playing my favorite  songs.. Keep connecting.. https://t.co/2DIIKx4MJn
"]

column2:
['* Hoisted the National Flag at MLA Office #SarvagnaNagar on #IndependenceDayIndia2020.

* Participated in a program to plant #Saplings at Hennur Bande. https://t.co/kU1ZW7EUfB

2/3 https://t.co/GKMR62fwxE

', 'Dear Residents,

', 'While International #CrudeOil prices are at its lowest, the prices of fuel have been going up constantly from past 21 days. Centre should take immediate measures to ensure that citizens who are already suffering due to #COVID19 in all aspects are not burdened further.
1/2
', '- Inaugurated Project of conversion of Overhead cables to Underground cables near Machalibetta Water Tank.

', '- Economic Mismanagement

- Crumbling GDP (growth slows to a 11 year low of 4.2%)

- Rural unemployment rate is highest at 25.09%

#6YearsIndiaInTears

column2:
['"Don't be afraid to share the good news! The stories are there but they haven't had much airtime." - @SineadGray on the future of PR after the pandemic #COVID19Comms
', '@SineadGray has some great advice for handling the media post-covid - being able to shift things around and be flexible is the key to success for a lot of campaigns at the time. Have a plan B and C in your pocket too. #COVID19Comms
', '"Find the local news angle. Covid has increased our connection to our communities and increased traffic to local news sites too" - media insights from our live webinar #COVID19Comms
', "'During 'phase 2' of covid19, many turned to social media to connect with brands.' - @DaveReyn0lds speaks on coronavirus media insights #Covid19comms
", '@DaveReyn0lds on #covid19comms: We‚Äôre much more community-focused than we‚Äôve ever been before, e.g. brands turning to social media to connect and interact with their audiences, like IKEA sharing their famous meatball recipe üçù
', '"The continued easing of lockdown and confinement measures dominate the headlines in Europe with an additional focus on the continued economic fallout of the virus."

For more on the global #COVID19 media coverage this week, check out our #coronavirus insights monitor here. https://t.co/zm99Ejwlss
', 'As the global infection rate passes 3 million, the media focus is on the economic effects of the Covid-19 pandemic, potential treatments, and how to cope with the ‚Äúnew normal‚Ä? Our weekly Insights Monitor shows a snapshot analysis of the media‚Äôs perception of #coronavirus. https://t.co/F2zimi7LYf
', 'Last week, North America, Latin America and Europe led the global coverage as the epicentre of the Covid-19 outbreak moves from Europe to the Americas. Take a look at our #coronavirus insights monitor for more on the discussion, posts and distribution in the media. https://t.co/ym6G6vWLTA
', "As worldwide infection rates top two million, the pandemic remains the focus of the global media agenda. South America leads the #COVID19 coverage as the spread of the virus accelerates on the continent.

Last week's coronavirus insights monitor tells us more... https://t.co/DaRF1wG0TY
", 'RT @MarketingWeekEd: #Coronavirus is only heightening the challenges facing journalists and media brands, but is also bringing trust and ac‚Ä¶
', 'Last week we hosted a webinar to address the growing PR concerns around the pandemic and provide tips on how brands can navigate the COVID-19 crisis.

Here are 10 key takeaways from our panel of industry professionals. #covid19comms #crisiscomms https://t.co/ebsLap7Nlm
', 'RT @source_tweets: Tuned in to the #Covid19Comms webinar with @CisionUK, keeping up to date on our comms knowledge during the #Coronavirus‚Ä¶
', 'Keep your brand profile up, work on human interest content but be ready and plan for the comeback. #covid19comms #moderncomms
', 'RT @paulasantos: Thanks @CisionUK for the #COVID19 Comms webinar! https://t.co/W4UZc6BBH9
', 'RT @Jenny_Sanchis: @PhilHall_PHA on #Covid19Comms "Remote working could become the new norm. People enjoy it, it is more cost-effective in‚Ä¶
', "Not everyone needs to have a voice right now as there is currently so much noise. You don't need to use the pandemic as a hook to get coverage. #covid19comms #moderncomms
", 'Be empathetic, positive and take your clients or audience on the journey with you. Everyone is understanding at this time.
#covid19comms #moderncomms
', "At this time of fake news, journalists are looking for stories that feel backed up with a level of authority - whether it's stats or an expert voice. #covid19comms #moderncomms
", 'Being transparent and human with your audience is important to create a community spirit. Use social media tools to achieve this. #covid19comms #moderncomms
', "Show that you're still open for business. Make sure you're adapting to different agendas and don't portray your brand as giving up. Be positive and show leadership. #covid19comms #moderncomms
", "If you have a natural way to get involved in the coronavirus conversation, then that's great but don't try and shoehorn your brand into the narrative if it doesn't fit. #covid19comms #moderncomms
", "RT @toomanylisas: 'Show you're adapting and prepare for comeback.' important and key business tips from @CisionUK #covid19comms
", 'Join us today at 3pm for our live webinar and learn how to approach your crisis comms during the covid-19 pandemic: https://t.co/Yj1vw4mRcy

#covid19comms #moderncomms #crisiscomms https://t.co/rv9Wqhonk3
', "#COVID19 dominated the media agenda once again this week, with Europe and North America leading global coverage as infection rates rise and nations implement lockdowns safety measures.

Our #coronavirus monitor attached shows you insights into this week's coverage. https://t.co/mSwyfJ2Xi1
", 'RT @90DigitalAgency: As a brand it can be difficult to know how you should communicate during #COVID2019, @CisionUK are hosting an online s‚Ä¶
', 'To address growing concerns around the COVID-19 pandemic, we have put together a panel of experts to share their best practices for brand crisis comms.

Join us for our live webinar on Tuesday 31 March, at 3pm.

REGISTER HERE: https://t.co/Yj1vw4mRcy

#covid19comms #moderncomms https://t.co/4wQKBXrblN
', 'Last week in the media, the #coronavirus discussion focused on the unprecedented and drastic government responses to the outbreak as well as the escalating economic effects and countermeasures. Our #COVID19 monitor attached shows you insights into the coverage last week. https://t.co/6DUuoDqYTe
', 'RT @ruxjosan: Amid #coronavirus crisis, PRs should:
- be authentically useful
- stop emailing unless to update (+ good time to show brand v‚Ä¶
', 'RT @Cision: Do not plan for an ‚Äúif‚Ä?scenario, do the ‚Äúwhen‚Ä? #COVID19Comms
', 'Reporting on the #COVID19 pandemic dominated the global media agenda during the week, supplanting almost all news coverage worldwide. Our #coronavirus monitor attached shows you insights into the coverage this week. https://t.co/KIQ5L207zM

['#Malaysian manufacturing production stabilised in August, sustaining the recovery from the #COVID-19 downturn. Headline #PMI dipped from 50.0 in July to 49.3 in August. Employment scaled back to greatest degree in survey so far. https://t.co/u2latOcje0 https://t.co/meDgNZCPk7
', 'Latest #PMI data for #Vietnam highlight ongoing effects of #COVID-19 on the manufacturing sector and challenges in trying to overcome them. Demand remained weak, with firms scaling back production accordingly in Aug. https://t.co/9l5GqMPQ0F https://t.co/PxngQNGoEd
', 'The #Philippines manufacturing sector headed into a steeper downturn in Aug as #COVID-19 quarantine measures in a number of provinces were tightened, according to #PMI data. New orders fell sharply, and output dropped for second straight month. https://t.co/TPRvwmk0JJ https://t.co/LesBDMJNMH
', '#Japanese business activity continued to contract in August, according to flash #PMI data, adding to concerns about the depth of the economic downturn and recovery pace. Demand still adversely affected by subdued trade and #COVID-19 measures.  More here: https://t.co/I8MLGYrjkN https://t.co/GU9PldVvNJ
', 'Flash #PMI data showed #Australian business activity falling back into decline in August as re-imposition of #COVID-19 measures in parts of the country disrupted business operations and hit demand, with the service sector particularly affected. More here: https://t.co/PFC3BetFxk https://t.co/HKtsB705Bv
', 'Flash August #PMI updates will be the highlight next week as analysts seek fresh insights into the prospect of further economic recovery amid a resurgence of #coronavirus in parts of the world and #lockdowns re-imposes in some cases. Read more #WeekAhead https://t.co/OwJgOEyuyb https://t.co/GCU9ZhZ1II
', 'July #PMI data signalled a stabilisation in business activity across the U.S. service sector, as companies continued to reopen following #COVID-19 lockdowns. New orders fell slightly, however, with client demand remaining subdued. Read more: https://t.co/ebBdxDFrTS https://t.co/0QyExQQqOv
', 'Brazilian service providers recorded another marked deterioration in business activity in July, as the #COVID-19 pandemic continued to weigh heavily on market demand. Levels of new work fell sharply, and firms made further job cuts. Read more: https://t.co/JqxyAmxLt2 https://t.co/EOfWHtxxKH
', "#PMI data show #China's service sector growth remained elevated in July as the economy recovers from #COVID-19. Growth rates of new business and activity remained strong, helping to support business confidence, which rose to the highest in over five years. https://t.co/z9fApv0P24 https://t.co/RPeUpUhX1w
", 'July #PMI data pointed to a marked deterioration in #HongKong SAR private sector conditions, representing a setback to economic recovery. The tightening of #COVID-19 measures in response to a rise in new infections dealt a new blow to the economy. https://t.co/uNgWpukAuH https://t.co/J9nPP22tvW
', '#Taiwanese manufacturing companies signalled a renewed improvement in operating conditions during July as the sector recovered from the impact of #COVID-19. Notably, output levels stabilised and new orders returned to growth. https://t.co/hleWiGwb0S https://t.co/ip2QufQxQ5
', "#PMI data showed another marked easing in the downturn across #Indonesia's manufacturing sector during July, adding to hopes that the worst of the impact of the #COVID-19 pandemic was felt in Q2. But the survey also points to a challenging recovery ahead. https://t.co/bSHoMhG6jA https://t.co/kXT4JJpocM
", "#Thailand's manufacturing sector deteriorated further in July, according to latest #PMI data, adding to concerns about the depth of the economic downturn as the impact of #COVID-19 pandemic continued to weigh heavily on the sector. https://t.co/YIrmITXPeA https://t.co/MlAe0Dk9sN
", "#Japan's manufacturing sector remained severely impacted by #COVID-19 and subsequent global growth downturn. But #PMI recovered some ground lost in the second quarter, helped by the smallest declines in output and new orders for five months during July. https://t.co/imPnaJ4mfN https://t.co/UNx0WsvTtK
", "After returning to growth in June, #PMI data showed #Vietnam's manufacturing sector took a step back in July, seeing declines in output and new orders as the #COVID-19 continued to impact business conditions. More here: https://t.co/nJRIg5zghI https://t.co/x0wawZFVr6
", "Latest Caixin #PMI signalled a solid improvement in the health of #China's manufacturing sector in July, as market conditions continued to recover from #COVID-19 outbreak.  Output and new orders up at fastest rates since Jan 2011. More here: https://t.co/WNvxTVTowS https://t.co/fNAc6vSuKC
", 'Insights into depth of #COVID-19 related economic downturns will be provided by Q2 GDP for #US, #Eurozone, #HongKong, #Taiwan next week while impact on companies will be revealed via US earnings updates from >800 firms. #FOMC also meets. #WeekAhead report: https://t.co/I1wVQ3rxkS https://t.co/E38NAnzipx
', 'The rebound in the #Australian economy from #COVID-19 lockdowns gathered pace in July, with business activity increasing markedly, according to flash #PMI data, adding to hopes that the economy could return to growth in the third quarter. Read more: https://t.co/9BdHuPLMQy https://t.co/d8soM2yqGF
', '#PMI data show #Australian services activity rose for the first time in five months during June amid a further easing of #COVID-19 restrictions. New sales also returned to growth while business sentiment improved. Read more https://t.co/pu8CRW9IO2 https://t.co/gWTnHsXVK5
', 'üá∫üá∏ U.S. manufacturing conditions deteriorated only fractionally in June. The #PMI registered a record 10-point rise to post 49.8, as the contraction in output slowed and new orders stabilised amid looser #COVID19 restrictions. Read more: https://t.co/2vn5fZUqfV https://t.co/CfsfSLgLvU
', "#Myanmar's goods producers showed signs of emerging
from the #COVID-19 crisis in June. Though the headline #PMI remained below 50.0, key indices for new orders and output both returned to growth territory for the first time since Feb. More here https://t.co/sxb74lKsBY https://t.co/NFfarpfa4m
", "Latest #PMI data showed a marked easing in the decline in #Indonesia's manufacturing sector during June as the country relaxed #COVID-19 restrictions. But recovery in coming months will be challenging as output and sales still falling at substantial rates. https://t.co/cHKnJOLkF9 https://t.co/kOHskLHTac
", "June #PMI showed that the downturn eased across #Taiwan's manufacturing sector as governments worldwide loosened #COVID-19 restrictions. Output, new work and employment all fell at softer rates compared to May, while business sentiment turned positive. https://t.co/wa5qSK235Z https://t.co/m6caMPP2St
", '#WeekAhead sees markets looking for further confirmation that the global economy has started to recover from the #COVID-19 impact, but also watch for signs of second wave infections. Key data include global #PMI surveys and US nonfarm payrolls. More here: https://t.co/TgDoRzGNjH https://t.co/1QYGvPitKU
', "Flash #PMI showed #Japan's business activity contracted sharply again in June despite an easing of #COVID-19 related measures. While the downturn slowed further, the economy continued to struggle amid global trade weakness. Read more: https://t.co/x4WKxjO4In https://t.co/mrS0Mhmv9L
", 'Flash #PMI pointed to a return to growth of #Australian private sector output in June amid a further loosening of restrictions related to #COVID-19. New orders stabilised, but firms continued to reduce employment as they operated below normal capacity. https://t.co/FVsFEfLm7O https://t.co/03fs9eGR1g
', "#PMI data showed a severe decline in #India's services activity in May amid #COVID-19 restrictions. Job shedding persisted into the month while confidence remained weak. Read more: https://t.co/NO90yQJzsK https://t.co/2QgXM8HI4e
", "#PMI data showed business activity across #Australia's service sector falling substantially in May as ongoing #COVID-19 measures continued to hit demand. But declines in both activity and new orders slowed as some restrictions were relaxed. Read more https://t.co/TedUHddKYr https://t.co/1ZAHGXcQOa
", 'Caixin #China #PMI data signalled the first increase in services activity for four months in May amid an easing of #COVID-19 measures. Both business activity and new orders expanded at the quickest rates since late 2010. Read more: https://t.co/39hPcFViiz https://t.co/f72qkwPBhv
', 'The Dutch manufacturing sector remained mired in a #COVID-19 induced downturn in May. The headline #PMI fell to 40.5 (April: 41.3) and was the lowest for eleven years. Output and new orders declined markedly, while job cuts continued. Read more: https://t.co/141C6P4lHy https://t.co/E7QfohdPbw
', "üá¨üáß UK Manufacturing #PMI rises to 40.7 in May (April: 32.6) to signal a further sharp downturn, but the pace of contraction eases from April's record. Output, new orders and employment all fell sharply again amid #COVID-19 restrictions. Read more: https://t.co/ety9bOTOmZ https://t.co/dcI0JrUAXM
", '#Australia manufacturing #PMI falls to all-time low as #COVID-19 measures hit output.  Output and purchasing activity both fell at record rates while demand weakened further. https://t.co/lJTIzH8h9b https://t.co/xm9xPF2npI
', '#PMI data showed Philippines manufacturers suffering a further hit to output from #COVID-19 during May. Restrictions in the capital and other cities continued to hit demand, with another steep fall in new orders recorded. https://t.co/RyqhDG8jt6 https://t.co/QlmRN5Mrmo
', '#Vietnam manufacturing #PMI rose from 32.7 in April to 42.7 in May, signalling a slower, but still sharp decline in the health of the sector. Output, new orders and employment all decreased at rates unseen before the #COVID-19 crisis. https://t.co/CS3FnqTirf https://t.co/vIK1cDDZla
', '#Japan manufacturing downturn gathers pace in May as global #COVID-19 pandemic significantly reduced workloads, limited production capacity and heavily disrupted supply chains. #PMI falls to 38.4 in May, lowest in over 11 years. https://t.co/nR2Fg4QhSX https://t.co/6pacGigXLB
', 'Easing of #COVID-19 restrictions led to a stronger rise in #China manufacturing output in May, which rose at the quickest for >9 years, according to Caixin #PMI. But demand remained subdued, largely due to a notable fall in export orders. https://t.co/rSiYsCA1zA https://t.co/jeH80oAMTy
', 'Next week sees #PMI surveys provide first major insights into global #economic trends in May, with clues sought not only the depth of #downturn but also the speed with which economies can recover from #COVID-19. Download our latest #WeekAhead report here: https://t.co/DTyh8NjQJf https://t.co/uwnudcgjgQ
', 'üá∫üá∏ Flash U.S. Composite #PMI at 36.4 in May to signal a further steep fall in output amid #COVID-19, although the decline softened from April as the economy began to reopen. Read more: https://t.co/XuxAb0689A https://t.co/HA5ZISBIi6
', 'Flash #PMI data next week will provide the first insights into whether major economies have bottomed out after some countries started to ease restrictions designed to contain the #COVID-19 outbreak in May. Read more in latest #WeekAhead report. https://t.co/1XACNvvv6W
', 'Service sector output in #Japan sank deeper into contraction
in April, with the rate of decline far surpassing that seen in #GFC and after the 2011 tsunami. Measures to stem the spread of #COVID-19 led to a survey-record decline in demand. #PMI Read more: https://t.co/eeNgBU8nWH https://t.co/gcjO6TBYCm
']

column2:
['Deputy Health Minister, Dr. Okoe Boye is using the fees other countries charge for #COVID19 PCR tests to justify the $150 being charged arriving passengers for the much cheaper & less effective antigen test.

Why not PCR then?

Full üìπ: https://t.co/GTpEoDiVsj

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/T4n4LGXmXL
', '93 new cases for August 28 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 44,298 with 42,963 recoveries/discharge and 276 deaths.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/4uijRFv6wC
', 'The #COVID19 test Ghana intends to charge $150 for is not the gold standard PCR test.

It is an antigen test according to Dr. Franklin Asiedu-Bekoe (@kofi1170) on #SurvivingCOVID19 yesterday. In which case the cost should be even cheaper.

üìπ https://t.co/FolIB67jQt https://t.co/RklxSFhsTc
', 'Travelers arriving in Rwanda must have a negative #COVID19 PCR test and undergo another PCR test at $60 on arrival and checked into designated hotels for a day while they await their results.

Those who test positive will be treated at their own cost.

#SurvivingCOV https://t.co/12tNO3ahwJ
', 'President Akufo-Addo of Ghana announces opening of Kotoka International Airport to commercial flights from Tuesday, September 1, 2020 after months of closure due to the #COVID19 pandemic.

Watch full üìπ for accompanying directives: https://t.co/csG1oqKjIy

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/n5zdEODrtW
', 'This morning on #SurvivingCOVID19:

Which #COVID19 safety protocols should schools have in place for their students, drawing lessons from the reopening for the final year students?

Please share with any parent you know.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/ghnZfHtVwV
', 'Fellow Ghanaians, #COVID19 Update No. 16 by President Akufo-Addo is at 8pm.

Anticipate an announcement on the reopening of Kotoka to international commercial flights as indicated in the last update as well as the reopening of pre-tertiary schools.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/PhB0gvi4L5
', 'Meanwhile six more deaths and 87 new cases reported for Aug. 27 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 44,205 confirmed since March with 42,777 recoveries/discharge and 276 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,201 samples have a positivity rate of 7.24%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/PnpYEfBZWj
', '169 new cases reported for August 26 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 44,118 confirmed since March with 42,581 recoveries/discharge and 270 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,738 samples have a positivity rate of 9.72%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/J2DF6jrI0C
', 'The latest update by GHS shows five regions in Ghana have no active case of #COVID19.

There are however 108 new cases for Aug. 25 (7%‚ûïrate), meaning coro is still lurking.

Pls continue to wear a mask and observe the protocols so you don‚Äôt become a statistic.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/qhVmLxHkLw
', 'Do you know of a school doing excellent work to keep its students safe from #COVID19?

What is it that they are doing? Do share your thoughts
', '124 new cases (52 for Aug. 23 & 72 for Aug. 24) take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 43,841 with 42,246 R/Ds and 270 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,497 samples have a ‚ûïrate of 8%.

Coronavirus is still lurking. Don‚Äôt take anything for granted.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/i71Wz9gMJZ
', 'Seven more deaths and 95 new cases take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 43,717 confirmed since March with 41,843 recoveries/discharge and 270 deaths.

The new cases for August 22, being tests on 1,144 samples have a positivity rate of 8.3%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/k5Jvo2d3pk
', 'Two more deaths and 117 new cases for August 21, take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 43,622 confirmed since March with 41,695 R/Ds and 263 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,606 samples have a positivity rate of 7%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/3a8YUBBzyr
', 'Despite some consensus #COVID19 is being ‚Äúcharitable‚Ä?to Ghana which has seen a consistent decline in active cases, scientists say investment must go into research for the full story.

They also believe we need to ramp up testing.

Ep.7 #SurvivingCOVID19

https://t.co/12lBTIf5yC
', "This morning on #SurvivingCOVID19, if many of us are not wearing masks and not observing the protocols even with all the mass gatherings, why are hospitals in Ghana not overwhelmed?

Is #COVID19 disappearing, hiding or we're just not seeking?

Join me here https://t.co/KoUeHsJ8MF https://t.co/nNc3HOIwOk
", 'The 180 new cases reported August 20 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 43,505 confirmed since March with 41,532 recoveries/discharge and 261 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,131 samples have a positivity rate of 16%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/hIuBhD47yk
', 'Though many flout #COVID19 preventive protocols such as masks, Ghana is not seeing that many sick people. Some say we‚Äôre not testing. But why then are we not seeing our hospitals overwhelmed?

Is the virus truly disappearing, hiding or we‚Äôre just not seeking?

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/tK9xaA35zq
', '65 new cases for August 19 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 43,325 confirmed since March with 41,408 recoveries/discharges and 261 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,100 samples have a positivity rate of 6%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/PXjJnSKJsV
', '5 more deaths and 166 new cases for Aug. 18 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 43,260 w/ 41,267 R/Ds & 261 deaths.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/IFfmw9mex6
', '8 more #COVID19 deaths and 101 new cases reported Aug. 17, take the case count in Ghana to 43,094 w/ 40,963 R/Ds & 256 deaths.

', 'Nine new deaths and 340 new cases reported on August 16 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 42,993 confirmed since March with 40,796 R/Ds and 248 deaths.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/hwrSU0n5wT
', 'President Nana Addo Dankwa Akufo-Addo says Ghana is putting in place measures to ensure every passenger who arrives by air at the Kotoka International Airport will be tested for #COVID19 when the airport is reopened, hopefully by September 1.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/u842Gpy3qb
', '322 new cases for August 14 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 42,532 confirmed since March with 40,362 R/Ds and 231 deaths.

', 'RT @nkquakyi: Join us at 11AM today for a discussion on adapting #COVID19 responses to our local African contexts!

#MaskUp #StopTheSpread
', "Tomorrow on Surviving #COVID19, should Ghana/Africa begin to look at home-grown prescriptions/solutions to contain the coronavirus pandemic seeing that our circumstances are different and the impact isn't the same?

Click to join; https://t.co/KoUeHsJ8MF

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/1viA4Bmfop
", '147 new cases reported August 13, take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 42,210 confirmed with 40,147 R/Ds and 232 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,307 samples have a positivity rate of 11%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/okoDf9lLZW
', 'Details of latest #COVID19 related deaths indicate 9 more deaths taking the toll to 232 even though the summaries show 231.

216 new cases also take total confirmed in Ghana to 42,063.

The Aug. 12 new cases, being tests on 1,420 samples have a ‚ûïrate of 15%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/tUyW7OKPkP
', 'The 122 new cases for August 11, take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 41,847 confirmed since March with 39,718 R/Ds and 223 deaths.

The new cases, being tests on 1,998 samples have a positivity rate of 6%.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/8d2KhgeyIG
', 'At the rate of decline in active #COVID19 cases, Ghana is likely to record zero soon. But will that mean we‚Äôve overcome the pandemic or cos we stopped testing?

The 153 new cases reported on Aug. 10, being tests on 1,262 samples, have a ‚ûïrate of 12%.

#StaySafe
#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/q1UMNjVlI0
', 'It‚Äôs curious that even though there‚Äôs been a decline in new cases, more deaths and ‚Äúinteresting‚Ä?positivity rates are being recorded.

#StaySafe
#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/hdWbmBKoUL
', 'The 192 new cases reported on August 8 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 41,404 confirmed since March with 39,055 R/Ds and 215 deaths.

', 'The 209 new cases reported on August 7 take the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 41,212 confirmed since March with 38,727 R/Ds and 215 deaths.

', 'What if Ghana Health Service announced next two weeks that it has no more #COVID19 active cases to report? Would that mean the end of the pandemic for Ghana?

', 'Seven more #COVID19 related deaths and 455 new cases take the case count in Ghana to 40,097 confirmed since March with 36,638 R/Ds and 206 deaths.

', 'The 567 new cases reported on August 3 takes the #COVID19 case count in Ghana to 39,642 confirmed since March with 36,384 R/Ds and 199 deaths.

', 'The day Ghana recorded the highest no. of #COVID19 cases remains June 26 (per sample date). The no. of cases has however increased to about 1,150 from 1K after a week.

It could increase as more backlogs are cleared, that is, if there are more June 26 samples.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/d0pEgjb5ur
', 'The eight latest #COVID19 related deaths reported for Aug. 2 in Ghana involve four females, one of them pregnant, and four males from Ashanti, Upper West & Volta regions aged 76, 70, 64, 35, 60, 55, 37 & 28.

#SurvivingCOVID19 https://t.co/aGW54Qc33r
', '8 more #COVID19 deaths and 1,263 new cases for Aug. 1 & 2(574) take the case count in Ghana to 39,075 confirmed since March w/ 35,563 R/Ds & 199 deaths.

column2:
['#COVID-19 has disrupted the multibillion-dollar micro #mobility industry. Before the crisis, the micro mobility industry was predicted to be a $300B to $500B market by 2030. Market forces can alter the course of what are hot sectors and troubled sectors.

https://t.co/PT8c4PH0nw
', '.#Covid19 pandemic has had an unprecedented impact on üáÆüá≥ businesses & more or so on startups. We need to come together & implement revival plans.

Look forward to having an engaging discussion with @deepkalra at #GlobalFintechFest today at 1:45 PM. https://t.co/VENvjX2xz5
', 'The fight against #coronavirus is nothing short of war. At our frontline, are our warriors, our #doctors. Thank you, doctors, for your service & dedication to helping Indians through this unprecedented time.

#SabsePehleSwasth @swasthorg https://t.co/HwK1AeWQwD
', '~286K Indians have recovered from #COVID. They have fought the virus & given hope to the rest of us.

This video talks about their #struggle. How acceptance is needed from rejection, isolation & stigma. #IndiaSaathTohBanegiBaat

Video Credits- @StartupsvsCovid https://t.co/mkwF2txg8R
', 'If you or any of your relatives have cold, cough, fever or difficulty in breathing, and are worried about #COVID19 symptoms, no need to step out. Consult #doctors for free from the comfort of your home through audio and video calls.

Visit https://t.co/g56kT3liyD (1/3)
', 'Spoke with @adhilshetty, CEO of @BankBazaar on how #Consumer behaviour has changed as a result of #Covid19 and what we need to embrace #change & act now.

Thanks Adhil. Really enjoyed our conversation:

https://t.co/NRlpPUwJCw
', 'Look forward to having an engaging discussion with @adhilshetty, CEO of @BankBazaar on how consumer behaviour has evolved in recent times due to #COVID19

Date: May 28 | Time: 2pm
RSVP here- https://t.co/f1hnPJseIT https://t.co/2v5ZvzG06M
', 'Thought provoking discussion with this dynamic panel @kiranshaw @drsangitareddy & @DipaliGoenka on how businesses must prepare & tackle challenges in these trying times! Watch this episode on @ETNOWlive tonight at 10:30 pm.
#COVID19 @sonalikrishna https://t.co/ak22BKt5SQ
', '.@NYTimes devoted an entire cover page to list 1000 #COVID19 victims. (1% of the current COVID death toll in the US)

By putting names to a number we acknowledge their life. They are more than a statistic. They are people who are loved and mourned and will be missed https://t.co/ONFqOh6Xuv
', 'I found this gut-wrenching. How our realities can be so different & how we occupy different worlds. This is not just because of #Covid19. Globally, people live in different worlds, & we are more & more disconnected from others who are not like us.
Video Credits: @Debjyotisaha217 https://t.co/dacADrW8JV
']

column2:
['In our latest photo blog you can see staff and community volunteers out in the community taking temperatures and pulse readings to safeguard the community. #CommunityShield #Covid19 #TrackandTrace

https://t.co/3lCcmjfykw https://t.co/8cmIqke71r
', "The 1984 Bhopal gas disaster, India left behind what may be the most at-risk population on earth. Gravely vulnerable to #COVID19 survivors set up a model shoestring 'Community Shield'. Learn more and support their efforts at: https://t.co/TKQiYOFETL https://t.co/pwI3KelIvK
", "The first point in our clinic's #COVID19 action plan is effective communication and awareness raising - Door to door, within communities and using technology. Here you can see this in action - using mobile phones to connect the community #CommunityShield

https://t.co/D760RhbnVU https://t.co/Vgvm2alBYI
", 'The team at our Sambhavna clinic are on the front line of the #covid19 response, but have put in place safety measures to ensure the clinic can still serve the gas affected community. #CommunityShield

Photo credit - Biju Nair https://t.co/kdbuA7Xy1Z
', 'Today we celebrate the younger #Community Health Volunteers on the front line of the fight against #COVID19 in Bhopal. Some as young as 15 have been working with our clinics to educate and safeguard the vulnerable.

https://t.co/D760RhbnVU

Photo - Biju Nair https://t.co/zCI48Q8U6x
', '#GivingTuesday Just ¬£2.50 pays a Community Health Worker‚Äôs expenses for a whole month. Please consider a donation or share this post to help gravely vulnerable Bhopal survivors protect themselves from #COVID19

https://t.co/ojhS8DimTj
', 'Children are helping community health volunteers as they put up #covid19 educational posters in their communities in #Bhopal. #MondayMotivation

photo - Biju Nair https://t.co/CSWEDh9lwI
', "Our latest #Coronavirus update - Including updates about Bhopal's lockdown, Bhopal's #CommunityShield and the Chingari Clinic.

https://t.co/uyGM7W2WZa
", 'From 8pm Bhopal will be back in lockdown due to rising cases of #Covid19.

Our clinics and #community health teams are working tirelessly to protect the vulnerable gas affected communities.

https://t.co/HzeQUmQefa
', 'Here are just some of the incredible Community Health Workers who are working with #volunteers and communities in Bhopal to protect the vulnerable and stem the spread of #Covid19 - https://t.co/D760RhbnVU https://t.co/hqvhbB5KG7
', 'Please consider a donation to our GoFundMe Appeal - As part of our #CommunityShield campaign we are raising funds for the vital #COVID19 response work happening in vulnerable Bhopal communities.

https://t.co/ojhS8DimTj https://t.co/J8S6C6MN00
', "Staff at our Sambhavna clinic check their patient's temperature before they enter to help stem the spread of #COVID19  - #CommunityShield

(photo - Biju Nair) https://t.co/My5EE7w1Nx
", 'Today as part of our #CommunityShield - #Covid19 response in Bhopal we launch our GoFundMe appeal.

https://t.co/ojhS8DimTj

Our work is expanding into neighbourhoods in which tens of thousands more gravely at-risk people live.

Please consider a donation to our appeal
', 'Our #CommunityShield is growing! Our clinics have expanded their work into another 20 communities in Bhopal. They will be recruiting and training volunteers within these communities to expand the community shield and stem the spread of #Covid19.

https://t.co/2qtn9xO7SS
', "The Bhopal Survivors' initial #Covid19 community mobilisation model is in 4 parts - #CommunityShield  #CommunityResponse

https://t.co/D760RhbnVU https://t.co/vymTyNRUDJ
", 'Lacking the natural defences to fight the coronavirus Bhopal survivors knew that personal safety depended on collective action. Their far-sightedness gifts the world a model approach against #Covid19. You can download the model here: https://t.co/D760RhbnVU #CommunityShield https://t.co/sILvERGADe
', 'The majority of gas survivors present multiple co-morbidities, therefore medical workers insist that Bhopal gas survivors are at least five times more vulnerable to #COVID19  #CommunityShield  https://t.co/D760RgTMxk https://t.co/OZud1twiH6
', "Join our #CommunityShield and receive Protocols for Community-Led Finding, Tracing, Protecting. A #Covid19 community mobilisation model. The Bhopal survivors' gift to towns, cities, countries around the world to help stem the spread

Join here: https://t.co/808s6XfcyC https://t.co/ee51tJYCTw
", "The #Telegraph have highlighted the survivors' #covid19 crisis 'Bhopal survivors succumb to Covid, 35 years after chemical disaster' #BhopalGasTragedy #Bhopal35

https://t.co/TSC5Hi1uPe
", 'On the day of Bhopal‚Äôs 1st #Covid19 death some of the poorest people on earth, lacking adequate #PPE, testing kits, financial or other resources agreed a demanding, dangerous plan of action #CommunityShield #Bhopal35 #CommunityResponse https://t.co/D760RgTMxk
(photo - Biju Nair) https://t.co/1qHOiN0RmY
', 'Gravely vulnerable, Bhopal survivors form a community shield. Their model community mobilisation has set the lead for govt and inspired a Global Humanitarian Network. Now their expertise gifts the world a model approach against #Covid19. #CommunityShield   https://t.co/D760RhbnVU https://t.co/Z7V3wrUlPd
', 'Gravely Vulnerable, Bhopal survivors have formed a community shield against #Covid19. Saturday we released an advert in the Guardian, in support of their work, today we officially launch our new campaign - Bhopal‚Äôs Community Shield  #CommunityShield https://t.co/D760RgTMxk https://t.co/xJviAVzOTU
', "For all our supporters in the UK we have an appeal out today in the Guardian newspaper - don't forget to get your copy! It's the start of our #Covid19 Campaign - Bhopal's Community Shield. Watch this space for more on this. #CommunityShield https://t.co/fiFnmknWAW
", 'While the Chingari clinic remains closed, medical staff and drivers from the clinic are still working tirelessly to support the city‚Äôs children during the Covid-19 lockdown. Read more here: https://t.co/zOUkB94qvz #Covid19 #Community https://t.co/kj0Sxhm3UU
', "@benramalingam interviewed staff at our clinics for ALNAP'S guidance for humanitarian responders to #COVID__19 -  We can all use his reflections on crisis fatigue #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek https://t.co/9VtuCaZbXE
", "'In Bhopal smartphones and improved internet coverage make it possible to communicate and share information more widely than ever before, and the community‚Äôs use of these tools is helping to stem the spread of #Covid19 and save lives on a daily basis.' https://t.co/iLQ2ILpR30 https://t.co/z7E8ttakML
", 'Here is the timeline of the arrival of #Covid19 in Bhopal and the actions taken by clinic staff and survivor groups in the city to battle its spread #CommunityResponse

https://t.co/wRQKg9aObe

Photo credit - Biju Nair https://t.co/qnc0ykcHOS
', "Anwar Ahmed is the 20th gas survivor to die from #covid19 in Bhopal, this is a tragedy - 'Turned away by BMHRC, gas victim dies of Covid-19' https://t.co/tOFHVdN1EM via @timesofindia
", 'Here is our latest #covid19 update - you can find more information on the government decision to work with survivor organisations to safeguard the gas-affected community in Bhopal #communityresponse

https://t.co/rYpnKLo3sU

Photo credit: Biju Nair https://t.co/w6Uex4iyQc
', "This is really good news for the gas-affected community in Bhopal #covid19 #testing 'Gas victims‚Ä?screening begins, finally' https://t.co/rJFCdOMxFg via @timesofindia
", 'A summary video for the @ALNAP guidance for humanitarian responders to #COVID__19  - this features photos from our Sambhavna clinic taken by @bijubhopal and staff from Sambhavna were interviewed for the report https://t.co/czk4XXXtH8
', 'You can read more about the innovative measures our clinics in #Bhopal have put in place within the community to stem the spread of #covid19 in our latest blog: https://t.co/DYnFyDHMDc https://t.co/NNaGz9fjvM
', 'Here is a direct link to the report, photos of the #covid19 response in Bhopal have been used throughout the report, including the front cover. These photos were taken by @bijubhopal from Sambhavna Clinic https://t.co/oBoLfhD4iO
', 'Staff at our Sambhavna clinic were interviewed for this report, we are pleased to see their #innovative and #communityhealth focussed response to #covid19 was used to help craft this excellent report and will go to help humanitarian organisations and communities around the world https://t.co/sguc8aCtRD
', "The number of gas survivor deaths is sadly now into double figures #covid19 #bhopalgastragedy '10th Covid death in Bhopal, all gas victims' https://t.co/a6nh5mootm via @timesofindia
", 'The death total in #Bhopal is now at 7, all were survivors of the 1984 gas disaster. The gas survivors are amongst the most vulnerable to the effects of #COVID1. Survivor groups call for action. Read our latest update here:

https://t.co/QcnnRKdhSJ https://t.co/2GUNR6rxxv
', 'Bhopal survivors commonly suffer acute respiratory disorders, hypertension and muscle weakness, cardiovascular diseases, diabetes, and various forms of cancer, all of which combine to place survivors at a severely elevated risk from #COVID19
', "More information on the gas survivors win back of BMHRC #Coronavirus #bhopalgastragedy | Bhopal Memorial Hospital and Research Centre handed back to gas tragedy survivors'  https://t.co/IZAPO4mVOw
", 'Yesterday Chingari vans and drivers took Sambhavna staff to more areas of Bhopal, Preet Nagar and Shiv Shakti Nagar to hand out #Covid19 pamphlets and raise awareness of safe practices #workingtogether #community https://t.co/uFDLVV3izx
', 'RT @barandbench: Conversion of hospital for Bhopal Gas Tragedy victims into COVID-19 Treatment Zone challenged in Supreme Court #Covid_19 #‚Ä¶
', 'These students are incredible! #covid19 #bhopal
COVID-19: Extending support to Bhopal gas tragedy victims https://t.co/BhZUXdPASa
', "A very interesting read from the Guardian, with Bhopal in complete lockdown now. #covid19
'Whether in the UK or the developing world, we're not all in coronavirus together'https://t.co/bMChm54kKK
", 'Here is a round up of what is currently happening for the gas-affected community in Bhopal. Please keep an eye on our blog, it will be updated regularly with current news. #COVID19 #Bhopal
https://t.co/uIYkSZQAQv https://t.co/8gU0PjS8Dg
', 'Our Chingari clinic is currently closed to all but emergencies, but their vans are out delivering vital medicines to the community instead of picking up children. Thank you to the staff and volunteers #COVID19 #Bhopal #community https://t.co/oVNRxkdh4o
', 'Staff at our Sambhavna and Chingari clinics have put together and distributed pamphlets to the gas-affected community to inform them of symptoms, hygiene and safety measures to help safeguard against the spread of #COVID19 #BhopalGasTragedy https://t.co/MnwrInjZoS

column2:
['The @WFDeaf_org @WFDYS have partnered with @IFHOH and @IFHOHYP on these recommendations for accessible communication during #COVID19 https://t.co/YjheLA0BTL
', 'Dr. Anthony Fauci presents at a @GallaudetU webinar with an American Sign Language #interpreter. I look forward to seeing the @WHO director @DrTedros #covid19 briefings also be accessible in International Sign. https://t.co/kW9uBTqtuu
', 'Thanks @WBG_SocialDev for this important webinar, deftly moderated by @McNhlapo, on ensuring quality, equitable education for all learners, including learners with disabilities, as we pivot towards distance education during #COVID19- and beyond. https://t.co/wA9cYTBldV
', 'RT @DeafZimTrust: #COVID19 #LockdownDownZim
Short Drama by @DeafZimTrust that shows the challenges faced by blind people during this pandem‚Ä¶
', 'RT @RupertRoniger: Persons w #disabilities from around the Globe share experiences during #Covid19: üé¶https://t.co/jqwRp7wjAp
Thanks to @GLA‚Ä¶
', 'The #WorldFederationOfTheDeaf Ordinary Member @rnudeaf reports on the impact of #covid19 https://t.co/LNF3c2PG7R
', 'RT @acadeafic: In this new blog/vlog, @JeminaNapier considers the impact of #COVID19 on not only current but especially future working cond‚Ä¶
', 'RT @IDA_CRPD_Forum: We need to see more sign language in mass media communications. Especially critical health information around #Covid19‚Ä¶
', '@UN Secretary General @antonioguterres shares important #healthforall information on #covid19accessibility and shows us what  #slaccessnow looks like with a sign language interpreter on screen.  Well done, Mr Secretary General! üôåüèºüôåüèºüôåüèº https://t.co/rDEJ4IwrVu
', 'The #WFD and @IDA_CRPD_Forum emphasize the @who and @UN need to ensure their briefings have full #COVID19Accessibility for all #PWDs and in sign languages for #deaf people with #slaccessnow   With #healthforall we can defeat the pandemic! https://t.co/QggkehsS9N
', 'Please share- and post your own video with these hashtags! Why is #covid19accessibility and #SLAccessNow important for YOU? (captioned version available on the #WFD Facebook and https://t.co/oeYFh8mNXP ) https://t.co/zTSWbWRCOK https://t.co/cH2N6Ljm6H
', 'It is vitally important that the @un and @who  keep to their mandate to provide #covid19access  In all formats.  Only with full information to everyone can we defeat #covid19! https://t.co/0RkwqwYsuK
', 'In my #WFD president interview with @thedailymoth  I stressed governments need to recognize national deaf associations are on the front line of the #COVID19 response, producing + sharing public health information to their members https://t.co/03ih6QsKqk
', 'The #WFD @WFDYS  and @DeafKidzIntl are committed to working with national governments and deaf associations to ensure no deaf child or youth are exposed to harm during #COVID19  Download our joint statement here https://t.co/Apo0Y3MM5p https://t.co/wuVLzkvvIE
', 'Thank you @lajkeating ! The #WFD is reaching out and meeting with our 125 national deaf association members in regional meetings this week and next, to share information and strategies to ensure deaf peoples rights during the  #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/cvGlEni9gI
', 'The #WFD and @wfdys make it clear that deaf students in higher education have the right to full access and continuity of education during the #Covid19 pandemic.  See the full statement in IS here, with a PDF download https://t.co/Vr7JamApCj https://t.co/QjByvOFROr
', 'Over 80 countries have national sign language interpreters at press conferences re #COVID19 !  This shows how deaf people‚Äôs #crpd  advocacy for our language rights has changed lives! https://t.co/RKbPiITeRB https://t.co/tDIiqFWfXn
', 'Well done UNICEF!  @uniceflac with #intlsign  #covid19 materials for children and parents! https://t.co/mFPylW2Ouz
', 'The #WFD Board and staff are united in asking us all to #stayhome during the #COVID19 pandemic #Stayhome and keep connected in our communities via video! We are #deafstrong! Full video: https://t.co/EoOfTZBfCd https://t.co/La7Zzg1jnz
', 'Good example from #Huelva, Spain of language congruent services by the public sector in a national #SignLanguage during the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/CSDNg71cil
', 'The #WFD has sent a letter to the @WHO We stand in solidarity with the @WHO during #coronavirus + offer our guidance and best practices in the provision of public health information in sign languages. https://t.co/w1PguNAnWN https://t.co/SBs54CD4ql
', 'What reason does @Statped have to take away sign language instruction  when other #SL ed centers ( @aslconnect and @GallaudetU ) are doing a massive shift to online learning in response to #COVID„É?9? Deaf children need #signlanguage instruction especially now w/ schools closed. https://t.co/mH9NsecXzF
', 'Well done @rnudeaf! Information in Rwandan Sign Language on the  #COVID19 by #WFD Ordinary Member Rwandan National Union of the Deaf. https://t.co/r98JUJ4zm1
', 'The #WFD and @WASLI_tweets have released Guidelines on Providing Access to Public Health Info in Nat. Sign Languages during #coronavirus   Get the PDF: https://t.co/hiX1ci54s0 .  And full IS version: https://t.co/Ov6bOe6ruw  Thread: 1/5 https://t.co/hmVXCMc6lI
', 'The #WFD has released a statement about the #coronavirus and is working to support our national deaf associations and global deaf communities in this time. Watch our website and Facebook for more info to come! https://t.co/nUlkrd6oQY
', 'Well done @FMoHealth for ensuring Ethiopian Sign Language access to important public health information during the #coronavirus pandemic! Other governments should follow their example! https://t.co/NVLRw0BKkF
', 'RT @mdemeulder: We are closely monitoring the situation with the #coronavirus. At this moment, we cannot guarantee the #DrDeaf Summer Schoo‚Ä¶
', 'Excellent information in Spanish Sign Language (LSE) from @CNSEinfo on sanitary measures during the #coronavirus https://t.co/AqljZDQQ8H
', 'The #WFD has just sent out a special issue of the #WFDNews to our members on the #CoronavirusOutbreak, highlighting the WFD/@WASLI_tweets Statement, best practice around the world, and an IS video from our partner @MillNeckManor. Join us as a member today! https://t.co/di6F1gI4cU https://t.co/1cEtxiEp0l
', 'Access to information on the #CoronavirusOutbreak in national sign languages is an obligation by all entities involved.  See the WFD and WASLI social media pages and webpages for the full statement! https://t.co/yvi0FlUQtd
']

column2:
['Onam greetings to all

May this colourful festival of flowers bring in the spirit of happiness, well-being and prosperity to all & give strength to overcome the challenges, including that of #COVID.

May this festival usher in growth, peace, development, good health & joy to all https://t.co/a3XidD4GKy
', "Namaste-  A Global greeting gesture

#COVID has changed the way people lead their lives & world leaders are no exception

Cautious of the spread of the virus through physical contact,'Namaste' is increasingly becoming the new norm @narendramodi @AmitShah @JPNadda @rajnathsingh https://t.co/0qFhnhEhxP
", 'Mask making emerges as a means of employment amid #COVID

Seizing the opportunity, the youth of #Hajaribagh started making #masks with an imprint of #SohraiKhovar art, which recently secured #GI tag.

They are hopeful that their sale would fetch them good returns. @smritiirani https://t.co/A1Q2NS2SEi
', 'Women of Umaria, Madhya Pradesh thank @narendramodi Govt for creating employment at local nursery under #PMNREGA & for giving them a 50% share in plants sale. They appreciate GoI for providing them jobs amid #COVID under @Himadri4Bjp @RitiPathakSidhi
https://t.co/CL2lzuC9Xm

', 'Gorakhnath Singh from Ranchi is thankful to @narendramodi Govt for the financial assistance he received under #PMKisan.
