column2:
['The tourism sector once had high hopes for travel bubbles.

National measures and fears of importing asymptomatic cases have burst those bubbles. https://t.co/6plDqn4MVp via @nytimes

#COVID19
', 'Desafortunadamente, la farmac√©utica Sanofi comunica que sus ensayos cl√≠nicos para tratamiento de casos graves de #COVID„É?9 no est√°n arrojando buenos resultados. https://t.co/0foLewIRBP
', 'La empresas de fabricaci√≥n de equipamiento m√©dico han conseguido capear la crisis del #COVID19 mejor que otros sectores.

Sin embargo, la ‚Äònueva normalidad‚Ä?de distanciamiento y restricciones presupuestarias puede ser problem√°tica. https://t.co/So12LhcyGV via @TheEconomist
', 'Una naci√≥n digital es tambi√©n aqu√©lla que es capaz de hacer transicionar su educaci√≥n a la red cuando la salud de alumnos y docentes est√° en juego.

De cara a un curso con #COVID„É?9, nos queda mucho por hacer por la educaci√≥n online. https://t.co/X0mao3y5tW via @CincoDiascom
', "In December 2019, tourism accounted for 12% of Spain's GDP and 13% of its total employment.

These 2020 figures are just breathtaking.

#COVID„É?9 https://t.co/R7B7J1AX9j
", 'La falta de reactivos para poder realizar las pruebas PCR correctamente puede ser devastadora para la contenci√≥n de #COVID19.

Agilizar los contratos de adquisici√≥n de estos reactivos, en colaboraci√≥n con los laboratorios, y cerrar nuevas adquisiciones debe ser una prioridad. https://t.co/2ukFNxYbLP
', 'El #COVID19 acapara los titulares, ¬øpero qu√© m√°s hay en la agenda sanitaria europea?

üî¨Plan de lucha contra el c√°ncer;
üíäEstrategia farmac√©utica para reducir nuestra dependencia del exterior;
üì≤Plan de datos sanitarios.
https://t.co/orNgB2JiG2 via @gerardofortuna
', 'üá∞üá∑ South Korea to introduce new restrictions on caf√©s and other venues to curb the second #COVID19 wave. https://t.co/1kgm5I0reT
', 'Espa√±a tomar√° parte en los ensayos cl√≠nicos de la vacuna contra el #COVID„É?9 de Johnson & Johnson.

Alrededor de una decena de vacunas est√°n en desarrollo en Espa√±a, pero ninguna hab√≠a avanzado hacia los ensayos cl√≠nicos. https://t.co/jV5XqLQDkk via @materia_ciencia
', "La pandemia de #COVID„É?9 ha hecho que los ciudadanos y los expertos demanden una Uni√≥n Europea con m√°s capacidad para hacer frente a retos de salud p√∫blica.

La nueva 'soberan√≠a europea' debe venir tambi√©n en el √°mbito sanitario. https://t.co/ivuFwLW6Hc via @ECFRMadrid
", 'ü¶†@WHO says symptomatic, suspect cases are a priority for #COVID19 testing, which should also be extended to their contacts regardless of whether they show symptoms. https://t.co/dY9WWyarL0 via @Reuters
', 'Pese a la creencia en el exterior de que las autoridades espa√±olas esconden datos de casos de #COVID19, seguimos presentando cifras escalofriantes. https://t.co/u2eDY6ao12
', 'Los ciudadanos de la mayor√≠a de pa√≠ses de este estudio de @YouGov consideran que Espa√±a es el pa√≠s que m√°s est√° mintiendo con sus cifras de casos y mortalidad por #COVID„É?9, y que lo est√° haciendo a prop√≥sito. https://t.co/VUHFJv2lwQ https://t.co/ATzxxtevEa
', 'Disponer cuanto antes de vacuna de #COVID19 puede tener un efecto tremendamente positivo en la recuperaci√≥n econ√≥mica y social.

La @ComisionEuropea cubrir√° a las farmac√©uticas por los riesgos a los que se enfrentan debido a la premura. https://t.co/FYw3iUtOjG via @el_pais
', 'Good news!

üî¨Moderna reports its #COVID_19 vaccine has a similar effect on both young and older subjects https://t.co/kCkYZQefaA via @Reuters

Also, so far over 13,000 participants have been enrolled in the study, 18% of which are Black, Latino, American Indian or Alaska Native.
', 'Pa√≠ses Bajos y B√©lgica detectan tambi√©n casos de reinfecci√≥n de #COVID19 en sujetos, creando debate entre expertos epidemiol√≥gicos https://t.co/zvh7dDX5Rj via @dwnews

Los anticuerpos de la primera infecci√≥n no pararon la segunda, pero podr√≠an haberla hecho mucho menos da√±ina.
', 'AstraZeneca, que tambi√©n est√° participando en el desarrollo de una vacuna contra el #COVID19, comienza un nuevo ensayo cl√≠nico de un tratamiento con anticuerpos. https://t.co/Y5L7XdaWOG via @Reuters

Este tratamiento podr√≠a utilizarse de forma preventiva y en pacientes.
', 'üá∞üá∑ Again, for all things #COVID19 look East. https://t.co/HzjmeVSXhp
', 'El Gobierno comunica a la @ComisionEuropea que se adhiere a su compra centralizada de vacunas para el #COVID19, lo que hace que Espa√±a tenga acceso a 31 millones de dosis. https://t.co/EzHfn4qZBd via @CincoDiascom
', 'While combustion vehicle sales are plunging due to the #COVID19 pandemic, electric vehicles are on the rise. https://t.co/D42DIJJhTh via @joshposaner

#EVs accounted for 8% of total car sales in the first half of 2020, up from  4% in 2019.

#auto
', 'La @ComisionEuropea propone al @EUCouncil que apruebe apoyo financiero de 21.300 millones de euros para Espa√±a bajo el Programa SURE. https://t.co/WS9vI0aZTk

Este programa tiene objetivo evitar la destrucci√≥n de empleo debido a la crisis provocada por la pandemia de #COVID19.
', 'La Presidenta @vonderleyen tambi√©n habr√≠a conseguido un acuerdo con Moderna para comprar 80 millones de dosis de su vacuna para el #COVID19. https://t.co/QK9ghEMoPq
', 'Un estudio del Reino Unido apunta a que la contaminaci√≥n del aire puede aumentar la mortalidad por #COVID19 en torno a un 6% https://t.co/0VgxwUWzbj via @cfresneda1

Investigaciones similares en Pa√≠ses Bajos y EEUU apuntaban a un incremento de la mortalidad de entre un 8-15%.
', 'Unos investigadores de Hong Kong detectan una segunda infecci√≥n de #COVID19 en un sujeto de 33 a√±os cuatro meses y medio despu√©s de su primer positivo.

Al parecer, se detect√≥ su caso -asintom√°tico- tras volver de un viaje en Espa√±a. https://t.co/18nmeJW3SF via @nytimes
', 'This October 2019 tweet suddenly became highly relevant.

#COVID19 https://t.co/ixy9xkdQa2
', "China is gaining ground in the fight against the #COVID19 pandemic, but there are important risks for the world if it were to follow Beijing's model, argue @SheenaGreitens & @JulianGewirtz.

https://t.co/SaQjBu6lVc via @ForeignAffairs
", 'Espa√±a es el pa√≠s de Europa donde la segunda ola de #COVID19 azota con m√°s fuerza.

Imprescindible repaso de @kikollan y @arturgalocha a los datos de la pandemia en el verano espa√±ol: https://t.co/35G87twopR via @el_pais
', "Ahead of #EarthOvershootDay, @UNFCCC calls for #climate action as social pressure mounts on governments for their record on the issue https://t.co/DGyozmI28j via @MaKaOro

Despite the #COVID19 pandemic, climate change is thought to be this century's major global challenge.
", 'üá∞üá∑ South Korea imposes unprecedented measures to halt a second wave of #COVID19 cases.

Large gatherings, nightlife, sports and religious events will be banned, while social distancing measures have been elevated https://t.co/5ES6rWaZbp via @euronews
', 'Bas√°ndose en los datos de la gripe de principios del S. XX, la @WHO estima que la pandemia de #COVID19 estar√° controlada en menos de dos a√±os.

Sin embargo, cada mes que se alarga supone un drama econ√≥mico y social para millones de personas. https://t.co/Dn2rtTwghK via @La_SER
', 'En los √∫ltimos tres meses la mitad de las empresas espa√±olas afectadas por el confinamiento en abril y mayo han conseguido empezar a recuperarse: https://t.co/oLScTERPMV via @expansioncom

Una mala gesti√≥n de los rebrotes de #COVID19 puede volver a empujarlas al cierre.
', 'La gesti√≥n de los rebrotes de #COVID19 en Espa√±a est√° fuera de control, y nuestra sociedad y nuestra econom√≠a no pueden permitirse un nuevo confinamiento.

La emergencia sanitaria ha abocado a m√°s de 240.000 PYMES al cierre: https://t.co/PZUsdHnjM5 via @expansioncom https://t.co/z1uxIqkRm6
', 'La pandemia de #COVID19 ha retrasado el #EarthOvershootDay al 22 de agosto, tres semanas m√°s tarde de lo que lleg√≥ en 2019.

Sin embargo, la tendencia de los √∫ltimos a√±os demuestra que queda mucho por hacer en materia de eficiencia de recursos naturales (via @EndOvershoot). https://t.co/a32ZMSwf8U
', 'La Presidenta @vonderleyen anuncia un nuevo acuerdo inminente con CureVac para adquirir 225 millones de dosis de su vacuna contra el #COVID„É?9. https://t.co/jq9cfKQmxu
', "Unfortunately, Spain is going under a second #COVID19 wave, but it seems the government is not up to the task of halting it.

Another harsh piece on Spain's handling of the health emergency by @rorihuela. https://t.co/Ls1DmXVj58
", 'The #COVID_19 has evidenced how important it is to stick together as one to tackle common problems.

#Space exploration will surely help in understanding life and future challenges down here, from climate change to global health https://t.co/fc4ivVuD3K via @AJEnglish

#research
', 'The #COVID„É?9 pandemic has prompted citizens and governments to relocate supply chains to Europe.

However, it will come at a cost. More accurately, $1 trillion according to estimates from @BankofAmerica https://t.co/0TrtamUdPk via @CNBC

#industry
', 'Spain once was a model for post-crisis recovery, but it might all go to waste if it does not get the #COVID19 pandemic right.

Harsh, but rather accurate op-ed by @FerdiGiugliano. https://t.co/MP1W27FfxQ
', 'European carmakers are however turning to online sales in an attempt to guarantee safety in times of #COVID19 https://t.co/sJnNrdwsdU via @SeekingAlpha

PSA expects to deliver as many as more than 100,000 vehicles directly to buyers‚Ä?homes.
', 'Pese a las afirmaciones de algunos dirigentes, m√°s tests PCR no significa necesariamente detectar m√°s positivos por #COVID19, sino controlar mejor la pandemia https://t.co/k26jeBOLSW via @carmenpaun

', 'US carmakers are turning to showroom safety and financing incentives to pump vehicle sales up after #COVID19 https://t.co/gDonLjZF0C via @seattletimes

', '#COVID19 has had a bigger impact on European carmakers that were already weaker before the crisis https://t.co/sPfp03dCER via @FitchRatings

', 'üá¶üá∫ La oposici√≥n laborista en Australia critica duramente la gesti√≥n del gobierno federal durante la pandemia de #COVID19, responsabiliz√°ndolo de la falta de coordinaci√≥n entre estados de la mancomunidad https://t.co/5MYMrBcU8x via @GuardianAus
', 'An #AI-powered software is helping healthcare professionals with a quick screening of #COVID19 patients at emergency rooms https://t.co/qQQt0fK5eb via @InnoOrigins

', 'üá¶üá∫ El PM de Australia, el conservador Scott Morrison, pide disculpas por la gesti√≥n del #COVID„É?9.

En particular, ha expresado que ‚Äúsiente profundamente‚Ä?que en algunos momentos la respuesta gubernamental haya sido insuficiente  https://t.co/sG19ybxNTJ via @GuardianAus
', 'La Presidenta @vonderleyen anuncia tambi√©n un acuerdo de la @ComisionEuropea con AstraZeneca por 400 millones de dosis de su vacuna contra la #COVID„É?9. https://t.co/OBuV9CId68
', 'La @ComisionEuropea ha conseguido un acuerdo con la empresa Johnson & Johnson para la compra de 200 millones de dosis de su vacuna experimental para el #COVID19.

', '#AI treatment for #COVID19 developed by @EITHealth has helped reduce mortality by about 50% https://t.co/mXUXEeYyBs via @HealthEuropa

', 'The much-needed #COVID_19 vaccine cannot come at the expense of public health.

', 'A√∫n a falta de que se garantice la interoperabilidad entre sistemas sanitarios auton√≥micos, no nos cuesta nada descargar #RadarCOVID.

']

column2:
['A comparison of data sources suggests that having now removed 5,377 deaths from the total count, the Government total number of deaths where a medical professional thinks #COVID19 was at least a factor in the death is now 12,000 lower than it should be. Graphic explains reasons. https://t.co/5r6z6WcXdn
', 'Early estimates for July 2020 indicate that there were 28.3 million paid employees in the UK, down 730,000 on March 2020 as the #COVID19 pandemic hit the UK labour market. https://t.co/M01wMcITAQ
', 'Discussion earlier with @BillDod_RT about the fact England has the worst #COVID19 mortality in Europe https://t.co/czTGchxHeO
', 'I have put this together but not much faith in the data. Data taken from https://t.co/04QiaCetb5 shows when adjusting for population size, Scotland and Wales have higher proportion of people in hospital with #Covid19 than England, yet the deaths all occurring in England. https://t.co/eNbBoDRXOc
', 'Useful thread to read on latest #Covid19UK infections in England. Good work by @Dr_D_Robertson https://t.co/jDLDtBXIP4
', 'The latest @ONS data provides some evidence people aged 85 and over who died earlier in the pandemic may have died in June, so #COVID19 brought forward their death by a few months. My go at explaining in this graphic. https://t.co/1XT6pr9ig2
', 'Update: Up to the 26 June 2020, estimate 69,390 excess deaths (above average) related to #COVID19

Deaths for week 26 of the year, w/e 26 June 2020 I estimate around 6% higher than average, down from 116% higher in mid-April. This is within the normal fluctuations year to year. https://t.co/vneco0H2W5
', 'Update: Up to the 20 June 2020, estimate 68,610 excess deaths (above average) related to the #COVID19 pandemic in the UK.

Deaths for week 25 of the year, w/e 19 June 2020 I estimate around 7% higher than average. This is within the normal fluctuations year to year. https://t.co/rK2L3eOcR7
', 'Update: Up to the 17 June 2020, estimate 68,400 excess deaths (above average) related to the #COVID19 pandemic in the UK.

Deaths for week 24 of the year, w/e 12 June 2020 I estimate around 9% higher than average. This down from 116% higher in mid-April. https://t.co/HSKaZBI0cU
', 'Update: Up to the 14 June 2020, estimate 68,920 excess deaths (above average) related to the #COVID19 pandemic in the UK.

Deaths over the past few weeks have been significantly lower than over the period of the pandemic. https://t.co/RFXkdkj1KU
', 'Update: Up to the 11 June 2020, estimate 68,675 excess deaths (above average) related to the #COVID19 pandemic in the UK. https://t.co/XiVzUlR8RA
', 'New @ONS plots the deaths involving #COVID19 up to the end of May. Clear to see the areas of the country most affected. In Wales it has been predominantly a virus of the South although currently deaths are not falling in the North at the moment. https://t.co/eME5HnkHTF
', 'Update: Up to the 07 June 2020, estimate 68,170 excess deaths (above average) related to the #COVID19 pandemic in the UK.

Deaths for week 23 of the year, w/e 05 June 2020 I estimate around 15% higher than average. This down from 116% higher in mid-April. https://t.co/oC8eftme7C
', 'Across the four nations of the UK the number of #COVID19  hospital admissions has been falling.

But in Wales hospital admissions per day have been relatively flat since 18 May 2020.

Admissions will be an early indicator of any rise in daily deaths. https://t.co/MZqjDDjFVA
', 'Update: Up to the 04 June 2020, estimate 67,810
excess deaths (above average) related to the #Covid19 UK pandemic.

This is 68% higher than the official Government number as that does not include people not tested. https://t.co/QLdFzGjcaH
', 'Update: Up to the 03 June 2020, estimate 67,550 excess deaths (above average) related to #Covid19 in the UK.

The rate of decline in excess deaths across the country has slowed down in recent weeks. But excess deaths much lower than the peak in the middle of April. https://t.co/KdKZGonzRs
', 'Update: Up to the 01 June 2020, estimate 67,140 excess UK deaths (above average) related to the #COVID19 pandemic

We are starting to see non-Covid related excess deaths below average. Longer term non-Covid deaths may rise because of missed treatment, for example cancer deaths https://t.co/CAT038WqI4
', 'Update: Another week has passed with more unfortunate deaths related to #Covid19 in the UK. The good news we have seen the seventh consecutive weekly fall in excess deaths. Estimate up to the 29 May 2020, 66,920 excess deaths (above average) in total related to the pandemic. https://t.co/VjtFFKvTDb
', 'Wales is the only part of the UK where people in hospital with #Covid19 is rising. This at a time there is tougher lockdown measures than its border country England. There are different testing policies in place. Thanks to @RichardClegg522 for highlighting this. https://t.co/ufhjPLtyHE
']

', 'Vor einem halben Jahr sind die ersten #COVID19-F√§lle in √ñsterreich aufgetreten. Unter https://t.co/yjaZYvFY9r findet sich eine Sammlung von Daten, die die gesellschaftlichen und wirtschaftlichen Auswirkungen der Pandemie zeigen.

', 'Sterbef√§lle nach Kalenderwochen sind jetzt bis inkl. KW23/2020 (1.-7. Juni) verf√ºgbar. Den aktualisierten Open-Data-Bestand gibt es hier: https://t.co/fc0io1w5k1 Updates erscheinen √ºblicherweise am Donnerstag - wir werden k√ºnftig nicht mehr explizit darauf hinweisen. #COVID19

https://t.co/mWmmFm44sS
#COVID„É?9 https://t.co/qfRgpeoJrC
', 'Der detaillierte Ergebnisbericht zur #COVID„É?9 -Pr√§valenzstudie ist nun auf unserer Website verf√ºgbar: https://t.co/ue8fYE67Rk
', 'In Zusammenarbeit mit @roteskreuzat und @MedUni_Vienna f√ºhrt @STATISTIK_AT zwischen 18. und 30.5. eine weitere COVID-19-Pr√§valenzstudie durch https://t.co/MVOHyznXM7 #COVID19

', 'Wie beurteilen Menschen ihr Wohlbefinden derzeit und welche Folgen werden als wahrscheinlich eingesch√§tzt - unsere aktuelle #Infografik gibt Infos zum Umgang mit #COVID19 https://t.co/URSvE0Gs25
', 'Laut #COVID-19 Pr√§valenzstudie von @STATISTIK_AT, @roteskreuzat und @MedUni_Vienna lag der Anteil SARS-CoV-2-Infizierter an der √∂sterreichischen Bev√∂lkerung ab 16 Jahren im Zeitraum 21. bis 24. April 2020 bei maximal 0,15% bzw. 10.823 Personen https://t.co/aQnxV6iPZU https://t.co/R2gl0oh5cJ

', 'Register today for a webinar discussing if and how the #COVID19 pandemic is impacting private business valuations, featuring Bryson Lord, tax expert at Economics Partners ‚Ä?a Ryan Company. https://t.co/5AeUGOseyd https://t.co/3LlTpjajdh

', 'A recent plan was submitted to New York Governor Andrew Cuomo on Friday, May 22, requesting an extension for the deadline on property tax bills for businesses economically impacted by #COVID19 until July 15, 2020. Learn more today.  https://t.co/qAWYtCXbWG https://t.co/OqL31gUm6B
', 'Hear our Chief People Officer @BridwellTony discuss the challenges #COVID19 has created in the way businesses operate and how the role of HR has been elevated as a strategic business partner. Register for the on-demand presentation today.

', 'Jurisdictions in Alabama have increased market values over that last two years. #COVID19, on top of an increased tax base, adds to the struggle property owners are facing. Learn more today.

', 'Dallas/Fort Worth is experiencing the impacts of the #COVID19 ‚Äúshelter-in-place‚Ä?orders, resulting in high unemployment and losses for many businesses. Learn more today about the possible Texas exemptions for COVID-19 damage.

https://t.co/CEFsfsHjWm https://t.co/xTkGjWChHQ
', 'The D.C. Council approved the COVID-19 Response Supplemental Emergency Amendment Act, which prohibits residential landlords from raising rent during the public health emergency. Learn more today.\xa0https://t.co/AaSGQ9IFvz #COVID„É?9 https://t.co/UAQcsURrQj
', 'Due to the economic downturn caused by #COVID19, there are certain common transfer pricing positions that need to be reassessed. Learn more today.

https://t.co/4saOH3hXJh https://t.co/HxtLDH42Af
', 'Ryan continues to monitor official government announcements and developments across Australia on a daily basis. Stay informed of the current tax changes by visiting our #COVID19 Australian Tax Developments page. Learn more today.

https://t.co/tPKWYYMVKn https://t.co/hzYNpRO6H0
', 'Ryan is exploring an opportunity for property #taxrelief due to the impact of #COVID19 on taxable property in California. Learn more today.

', 'We are excited to announce that Ryan Principal @JasonDeCuir has been appointed as Chairman of a private-sector task force to restart Louisiana‚Äôs economy in the aftermath of the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/rfdOmEYoPJ https://t.co/7yoSROaT0Z
', 'The New York Department of Taxation and Finance is temporarily accepting digital signatures on documents related to the determination or collection of tax liabilities. Learn more today. https://t.co/OgJVDUS24c #covid19 #taxrelief https://t.co/MIAon5V1iV
', 'In what could become a growing trend, one New Jersey municipality is granting forgiveness of penalty and interest on late real estate tax payments. Learn more today.  #covid19 #taxrelief

', 'Ryan is exploring potential property #taxrelief as a result of harm caused by #COVID19 to real and business personal property in Texas. Learn more today how your business could be impacted. https://t.co/2XLaOD4D6u https://t.co/8gDDeHtG4u
', 'The New York 2020-2021 budget bill will not adopt the CARES Act increased interest deduction, as the state‚Äôs approach is to lessen additional budgetary impacts. Learn more today. https://t.co/GF4NwL5rLo #covid19 #taxrelief #CARESAct https://t.co/kr2mb1J7Uo
', 'Businesses must be able to discern which programs or incentives they qualify for without unknowingly double-dipping or invalidating credits or loan forgiveness of federal or state funds. Learn more today. https://t.co/UtomoPcPgy #covid19 #taxrelief https://t.co/14OMBAp30N
', 'On March 19, 2020, Governor Eric Holcomb (@HolcombForIN) issued Indiana Executive Order 20-05 (EO 20-05), which extends several Indiana property tax deadlines. Learn more about how this implementation could impact your business. #covid19taxupdates https://t.co/bK0p25av8K https://t.co/BCfdNlONhM
', 'As of Monday, March 16, 2020, the Louisiana Governor suspends all legal deadlines and Legislature has recessed the 2020 Regular Session due to the #COVID19 pandemic. Learn more today how this could impact your business. https://t.co/XXMNYhupE6 https://t.co/DTImSeWnqO
', 'Keep informed of the ever-changing news and jurisdictional updates by visiting our dedicated #COVID19 site. https://t.co/FS8Cgtfv04 https://t.co/5J5uuNj1uH

column2:
['Kicking off our China Investor Forum 2020, @SonalVarma10 talks about the economic outlook of #Asia in light of the #Covid19 pandemic. #nomuraforum https://t.co/lRGbUx28Np
', 'Some argue that #Covid19 has diminished #climatechange as a priority, and it could be difficult to resurrect. However, we believe the #economic reset will act as a blessing in disguise; uniting a call for action against climate change. https://t.co/EFC4e87VaP
', 'We are pleased to announce US$1 million in matched #donations from our employees around the world to help in the global fight against #coronavirus. https://t.co/Bj8y6MYES4 https://t.co/gHur34hr2G
', '#Covid19 has seen the emergence of online teaching at a new and wider scale. However, this method of #education is expected to be a long-term effect of the pandemic, particularly in #China. Our analysts explain further: https://t.co/oouqkbOltI. https://t.co/WirLEeyIj0
', 'Continuing on from our previous report on the world post #Covid19, our analysts explain further on the impact this global pandemic will have on the world #economy. https://t.co/gGIxLy3aJn https://t.co/bNzqtr4DtC
', 'As the world continues to remain in the grip of #Covid19, it serves as a catalyst for change, shaping the world for decades to come. Our analysts, led by @RobSubby, give us an insight on how the world will change in the medium-term: https://t.co/bFb7QhYQnJ. https://t.co/IoE5dbZ4ju
', 'In their recent article for @UnravelSocial, @RobSubby, Head of Global Macro Research, and Rebecca Wang, explain how #emergingmarkets in #Asia stand a better chance at economic recovery from #Covid19 than others: https://t.co/lRZDDNiy1J.
', 'Despite #China being one of the first major economies to open up after #Covid19, it is still a long way away from a full recovery. Our analysts explain here: https://t.co/2VzUa84n0Q. https://t.co/UL4FtAVL34
', "New digital #trading platforms are providing opportunities for investors looking to trade #FX options. The #COVID19 pandemic, combined with regulatory requirements, and clients' drive for efficiency have led to these exciting developments.

Find out more: https://t.co/sAhhPT6cwz
", 'A growing cohort of marginally attached workers could flood the ranks of the #unemployed in #Asia if a new wave of #COVID19 cases emerges or when an exports slump hits the region, write our #economists @RobSubby and @SonalVarma10 in @NAR https://t.co/JE4F6w3wTX https://t.co/T0USOJDSWa
', 'At a recent panel discussion on ‚Ä?Diversity after #Covid19‚Ä?hosted by @ASIFMAnews, Aleem Jivraj, our #GlobalMarkets COO in #Asia, says it‚Äôs important to step up for female employees and colleagues during the pandemic and after. https://t.co/3iMOdBgw2X
', 'With lockdowns imposed by #Covid19 easing in different parts of the world, what does this mean for the global #auto industry? How has the pandemic changed commuting patterns, and are we on our way to a recovery? Find out from our analysts: https://t.co/Aa2dtlqrrH. https://t.co/wqn5FATvwt
', 'With #Covid19 being a common factor affecting many industries, it has also impacted capital markets. What does that mean for #sustainablefinance? Our analysts tell us here: https://t.co/DY6IvxY3tC. https://t.co/JiyBKfQza7
', 'Unsurprisingly, the #hospital sector has been impacted by the #Covid19 outbreak. At our recent #nomuraforum, our analysts explained how areas such as #China, #ASEAN and #India have been dealing with the pandemic and what can be expected in the future. https://t.co/Ej4Ht7SKmh https://t.co/UN1VgNtExc
', 'In our latest report, we develop a visual tool which helps assess the risk of a second wave of #Covid19 in 45 major economies as they start to reopen. Who is on track to recovery and who is at most risk? Find out here: https://t.co/fi4MwesXzE. https://t.co/8KCfo0139X
', 'In our latest Fireside Chat episode, our Head of Global Macro Research discusses an outlook for Global growth, the unconventional monetary policies rising from Emerging Markets & the likelihood of a second wave of #COVID19

Listen to the full episode here: https://t.co/ru8uwTmDXS https://t.co/N7H0wZotOg
', "Two countries who've performed well in the fight against #COVID19 are Australia & New Zealand. In our latest #podcast our regional Rates Strategist Andrew Ticehurst discusses how they've achieved this, and what the next steps for their economy could be. https://t.co/iN4mc8c9Uh
", 'Our chief #economist for India and Asia ex-Japan, @SonalVarma10 in conversation with @MitaliLive for @orfonline on what the economic recovery could like for #India after #COVID19. Watch here: https://t.co/GB26Rl23Fe
', 'How does the Federal Reserve plan on combating #COVID19 ? Our Chief US Economist outlines the potential outcomes we could see after their meeting this week. Click below to listen to our latest Fireside podcast: https://t.co/btt6z4Yo3O

column2:
['(See above tweet)at risk therefore they no longer will wear the PPE required when he was thought high risk when carrying out care at home  @JonAshworth @Keir_Starmer @DrRosena @DailyMirror @guardian @KayBurley @BBCNews #Covid19UK #NHS @NHSEngland @ObserverUK @SkyNews @BBCHughPym
', '@MattHancock #Coronavirusuk Oxford vaccine is being tested on participants aged 18 to 55 with no associated health conditions and therefore will NOT be tested on the very groups who are highest risk. It will not be safe or licensed for them @BBCHughPym @Keir_Starmer @JonAshworth
', 'Lightbulb moment. Before #MECFS I dealt with stress by dancing, going out, talking with friends or family, exercising, drinking, clubbing, laughing lots, going out for dinner, learning something new. No wonder #COVID19 anxiety hit so hard my life no longer has any of those in it!
', "from #COVID„É?9. They appear surprised, as if it's a novelty, an artifact of the Virus. It's not. It's Myalgic Encephalopathy - ME. ME is a multi system neurological disorder classified as such by the World Health Organisation. It already is known to be caused by viral infections
", "@MattHancock @grantshapps Why are you not implementing stricter hygiene standards for take away food establishments? Isolation is ruined if food is prepared and packed by someone with #Covid19UK who isn't wearing gloves or a face mask. Literally sending it into our homes ... https://t.co/n8U7DKmey4
", "@BorisJohnson I've just read your lockdown roadmap. How can lifting ANY restriction be considered safe when no-one aside from hospital patients or Keyworkers are being tested? No announcement about teacing?? Coronavirus has gone then, has it ?? #lockdownextension #Covid19UK
", "#coronavirusvaccine #oxforduniversity the vaccine is being trialled using participants between 18 and 55 years old. The most vulnerable group are older than this. Therefore it can't be reliably used in the older age group! @KayBurley @guardian @BBCHughPym @DrRosena @Keir_Starmer
", "@MattHancock A Met Police Officer living in a London suburb was told the next open slot for a frontline emergency worker #Covid_19 test is in BELFAST.  IRELAND. Proof of ID is needed checked against car registration, people don't drive!! Is the system working? Is it hell. #test
", '@Telegraph read your Oxford Vaccine article. Problem is participants are aged 18 to 55. As older age group than 55 more at risk from #coronavirusuk will Oxford confidently extrapolate trial results to them? @DrRosena @guardian @BethRigby @BBCHughPym @SkyNews #vaccines
', 'RT. You know those Keyworkers we clap every Thursday evening? Well, the Fire Brigade say that under cover of the Covid crisis, the @Conservatives are pushing through service cuts. #firebrigade #UK #COVID19 #Conservatives https://t.co/QyYzBU3HS3
', '@MattHancock Re: offering money to the families of frontline workers who died. Will that come with a contractual clause saying that if accepted they will not sue for loss under UK or EU Corporate Manslaughter legislation? @Keir_Starmer @JonAshworth #coronavirus @BorisJohnson
', "In the last week my old friend's mother and father BOTH passed away in different care homes of #COVID19. They were infected by staff with no effective #PPE and a lack of direction early on by @MattHancock regarding safeguarding vulnerable people in care. RIP. ‚ô•Ô∏è #carehomes
", "Before I close twitter for a few hours, I've heard very good things about this video. The doctor shows breathing techniques he says are crucial to help during #COVID19 could help when recovering and still coughing or breathless too. Stay well ‚ô•Ô∏è ü§ó ‚ô•Ô∏è X https://t.co/bFMNGKahJ5
", "#COVID19 the upshot is this. IF it's  going to Covid usually takes a downward turn at about 8 days. They look for temperature, pain, if you're coughing blood or mucus, whether your symptoms interrupt you carrying out normal household tasks. ie so breathless you can't talk or walk
", "It's been one of those days. Scared by ongoing breathlessness after #Covid_19 I called #nhs111 They were fantastic. Within 2 hours 3 Nurses and 1 Doctor phoned. Each assessed my symptoms, took a history and EVERY ONE of them called #MECFS a neurological disorder !! Awesome work.
"]
